<b>Last Updated: </b><i>May 19, 2025.</i>

<br/><br/>

<h2>What I do:</h2>
<hr/>
<ul>
  <li>I build front-end websites using <b>React</b> or plain <b>HTML</b>, <b>CSS</b>, <b>JavaScript</b>, and occasionally <b>jQuery</b>.</li>
  <li>I develop full-stack applications with <b>React</b> and <b>Firebase</b>.</li>
  <li>I create responsive websites that work well on both desktop and mobile devices.</li>
  <li>I develop desktop apps using <b>Python</b> with <b>Tkinter</b> or <b>Custom Tkinter</b>.</li>
  <li>I build mobile apps using <b>React Native</b> and <b>Expo Go</b>.</li>
  <li>I design logos exclusively for specific projects.</li>
  <li>I offer deployment services for <b>React</b> websites, with or without <b>Firebase</b>, excluding custom domain setup.</li>
  <li>I deliver the <b>Source Code</b> and final <b>Product</b> via GitHub or private messaging after full payment is received.</li>
</ul>

<br/>

<h2>What I don't do:</h2>
<hr/>
<ul>
  <li>I don't develop or deploy websites using PHP + MySQL.</li>
  <li>I don't offer graphic design services, as I'm not a graphic artist.</li>
  <li>I don't provide web hosting; I use third-party hosting platforms.</li>
  <li>I don't publish desktop or mobile apps to stores like Play Store or App Store—clients must handle publishing.</li>
  <li>I don't create 3D models, as I'm not a 3D artist.</li>
  <li>I don't manage custom domain names for React sites. Clients must provide their domain, or opt for free domains like <u>netlify.app</u> or <u>vercel.app</u>.</li>
  <li>I don't take on long-term projects (over 3 months); I focus on short-term tasks.</li>
  <li>I don't develop games.</li>
  <li>I don't provide production-ready cloud databases; clients must set up their own. Local databases are not included.</li>
  <li>I don't assess system/network vulnerabilities; I'm not a cybersecurity professional.</li>
</ul>

<br/>

<h2>Project Terms & Conditions</h2>
<hr/>

<h4>Payment Terms</h4>
<ul>
  <li>I may or not require a <b>downpayment</b> before starting any project. The amount will be discussed and agreed upon in advance (typically 25%).</li>
  <li>I only accept payments via <b>PayPal</b>, <b>Gcash</b>, or other platform-specific payment methods (as agreed upon).</li>
  <li>Failure to complete the full payment within the agreed time will result in project termination, regardless of the partial amount paid.</li>
</ul>

<br/>

<h4>Acceptance</h4>
<span>I reserve the right to decline a project if the timeline provided by the client is deemed unreasonable. A project will only commence once both parties agree on the scope and deadline. I require project contract to avoid conflicts and legal consequences before project development starts which will be provided by me and the terms must be accepted by the client.</span><br/>

<br/>

<h4>Scope of Work</h4>
<span>As a web, desktop app, and mobile app developer, I am only limited to developing these system and does not include tracing, reverse code engineering, making graphics, drawing, audio recording, image production, file safe-keeping, project backups, etc... as also stated in my <b>What I don't do</b> section.</span><br/>

<br/>

<h4>Termination and Cancellation</h4>
<span>In the event of project cancellation or termination, a refund of 50% of the total cost will be issued. Cancellation by the client halts all work immediately. I may cancel the project under circumstances such as late payment, significant changes, misconduct, technical issues, or personal emergencies.</span><br/>

<br/>

<h4>Delivery</h4>
<span>All the project build and source code files are to be delivered via github, or any platform in which the I and the client have agreed upon.</span><br/>

<br/>

<h4>Ownership, Confidentiality & Intellectual Property</h4>
<span>
All project-related materials will remain confidential and will not be shared, published, or made open-source without the client's explicit permission, unless the content is clearly intended for public release. Ownership of the project—including source code and deliverables—will be fully transferred to the client only after complete payment has been received. Until then, the project remains my sole intellectual property.
</span><br/>

<br/>

<h4>Completion Support</h4>
<span>I offer maximum <b>3 days of free support</b> after project completion for minor issues. Any major issues will incur additional charges.</span><br/>

<br/>

<h4>Project Changes</h4>
<span>Any changes or additional requests during the development process will be subject to additional costs, as it may affect the project scope and deadline.</span><br/>

<br/>

<h4>Working Hours</h4>
<span>As a college student, I strive to balance my education with my freelance work. I typically work during evenings and weekends, but please note that project timelines may be affected by my academic schedule.</span><br/>

<br/><br/>

<h2>Conflict & Resolution</h2>
<hr/>

<span>In the event of a conflict, these terms will serve as the primary reference for resolution. Where inconsistencies arise between these terms and any other documentation or communication, these terms shall prevail unless explicitly stated otherwise in a written agreement by both parties.</span>
